obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (37102)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00003_198558_1517807326430&sectionId=37102&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00003_198558_1517807326430
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Intelligence`
  line `Organisations (Restriction of Rights) Act, 1985.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 9th December, 1985, vide notification No. S.O. 885(E), dated 9th December, 1985, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (37103)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00003_198558_1517807326430&sectionId=37103&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00003_198558_1517807326430
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) "Intelligence Organisation" means any organisation established by the Central Government`
  line `for purposes of intelligence or counter-intelligence and specified in the Schedule;`
  line
  line `(b) "member of an Intelligence Organisation" means any person appointed to, or employed in,`
  line `any Intelligence Organisation;`
  line
  line `(c) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (37104)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Restrictions respecting right to form association, freedom of speech, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00003_198558_1517807326430&sectionId=37104&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00003_198558_1517807326430
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) No member of`
  line `an Intelligence Organisation shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) be a member of, or be associated in any way with, any trade union, labour union, political`
  line `association or with any class of trade unions, labour unions or political associations; or`
  line
  line `(b) be a member of, or be associated in any way with, or raise funds for, or hold office in, or`
  line `function in any other manner for, any other society, institution, association or organisation that is not`
  line `recognised by the Central Government as part of the Intelligence Organisation of which he is a`
  line `member or is not of a purely social, recreational or religious nature; or`
  line
  line `(c) communicate with the press or publish or cause to be published any book, letter, pamphlet,`
  line `poster or other document except with the prior permission of the head of the Intelligence`
  line `Organisation; or`
  line
  line `(d) except for purposes of official duty, contact, or communicate with any person on any matter`
  line `relating to functioning, structure, personnel or organisational affairs of the Intelligence Organisation`
  line `of which he is a member;`
  line
  line `(e) use the name of the Intelligence Organisation of which he is a member for purposes not`
  line `authorised by the head of the Intelligence Organisation or in any other manner except for purposes`
  line `relating to the official work and functioning of the Organisation itself.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—If any question arises as to whether any society, institution, association or organisation`
  line `is of a purely social, recreational or religious nature under clause (b) of this sub-section, the decision of`
  line `the Central Government thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `(2) No member of an Intelligence Organisation, shall participate in, or address, any meeting or take`
  line `part in any demonstration organised by any body of persons for any political purposes or for such other`
  line `purposes as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (37105)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title Penalty.
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00003_198558_1517807326430&sectionId=37105&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00003_198558_1517807326430
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Any person who contravenes any of the provisions of section 3 shall, without prejudice`
  line `to any other action that may be taken against him, be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to two years, or with fine which may extend to two thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (37106)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Offences to be cognizable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00003_198558_1517807326430&sectionId=37106&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00003_198558_1517807326430
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974),all offences punishable under section 4 shall be cognizable.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (37107)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Power to amend Schedule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00003_198558_1517807326430&sectionId=37107&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00003_198558_1517807326430
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, be notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, amend the Schedule by including therein any other organisation established by the Central`
  line `Government for purposes of intelligence or counter-intelligence or by omitting therefrom any`
  line `organisation already specified therein and on the publication of the notification, such organisation shall be`
  line `deemed to be specified in, or, as the case may be, omitted from, the Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every notification issued under sub-section (1) shall, as soon as may be after it is issued,`
  line `be laid before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (37108)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_39_65_00003_198558_1517807326430&sectionId=37108&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_39_65_00003_198558_1517807326430
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may`
  line `be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
